# Clean Code Rules

Follow:

- SOLID principles
- DRY
- KISS
- YAGNI

Functions:

- Keep functions small.
- One responsibility per function.
- Avoid deeply nested conditions.
- Prefer guard clauses.
- Use meaningful names.

Types:

- Avoid any.
- Prefer explicit types.
- Model invalid states as impossible.
- Types should have there own files

Errors:

- Handle errors explicitly.
- Never swallow exceptions.
- Provide useful error messages.

Comments:

Do not comment obvious code.

Comments should explain:

- why something exists
- non-obvious tradeoffs
- business decisions

Design patterns:

If you use a design pattern:
The function or class name must contain the pattern name
You MUST add a comment directly above it:

Example:

// Strategy Pattern
// Used because multiple algorithms can be swapped without changing the caller.

Explain:

- pattern name
- why it is used
- what problem it solves

Do not use patterns unnecessarily.

Never touch the backend code
